                <div class="tab-content">
                  <p>
                    Mathematician Michael Goff and designer John van der Harst met via the Nashville
                    Peace and Justice Center, and worked together in Recycling Advocates of Middle Tennessee.&nbsp;
                    Both continued to work in various other organizations as well -- some with each other, and others
                    apart.&nbsp; Discussions continued over what worked and didn't.&nbsp;
                  </p>
                  <br>
                  <p>
                    Both wanted to maximize their effect. Each had prior preferences for future work, but
                    conservatively chose to work together first on fundamental analysis which would properly
                    prioritize choices systematically.&nbsp; That was, and is, Urban Cruise Ship.
                  </p>
                </div>
